whats the difference between safe and unsafe staking ?

Safe staking adds a price limit (threshold) you are willing to go to in-case the price changes between you adding stake and it actually executing on the chain. 

You can define the % using `--threshold 0.05` or `--threshold 0.1` etc

There is also support for partial transactions. 
Lets say you are staking and you saw the price of `1.0`, you also set the threshold as `0.05` (5%) (limit becomes 1.05). 
It is possible that not all of your transaction will be able to execute with this price, but a partial amount will. 

In this case, if you pass in `--partial`, it will partially add stake till where the price is respected and wont stake the remaining amount. 
If you pass `--no-partial`, if the entire stake isnt able to execute within the threshold, the transaction is rejected. 


All of this can be skipped and you can stake like we currently do using `--unsafe` flag or just update the field in your config using `btcli config set`.
